-- Hungary central bank cuts rates by 10 bps to new low of 2.4 pct
-- 
-- Tue May 27, 2014 08:04AM EDT
-- None



BUDAPEST, May 27 (Reuters) - The National Bank of Hungary cut its base rate by another 10 basis points on Tuesday, bringing it to a record low 2.4 percent <NBHI>, below the benchmark in regional heavyweight Poland.

The 22nd successive monthly reduction in the base rate <NBHI> was forecast by most analysts polled by Reuters last week. [ID:nL6N0O91IQ] The forint <EURHUF=D3> traded at 303.61 versus the euro, a tad firmer than 303.70 just before the announcement.